Malaysia Stocks: Formis Resources, KKB Engineering, Unisem

-- B y   C h a n   T i e n   H i n
-- 
2011-07-29T09:26:17Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-29/malaysia-stocks-dutaland-formis-kkb-engineering-unisem.html
Shares of the following companies
had unusual moves in Malaysia trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of the 5 p.m. local-time close in
Kuala Lumpur.  The  FTSE Bursa Malaysia KLCI (FBMKLCI)  Index declined 3.10 points, or
0.2 percent, to 1,548.81, the lowest close since June 14. The
index dropped 1.9 percent this month, the biggest monthly drop
since May 2010.        Formis Resources Bhd. (FMRB)   dropped 1.9 percent to 76.5
sen, the largest loss since July 12. Red Zone Development Sdn.
emerged as a substantial shareholder in Formis after buying a
16.4 percent stake in the  software company , a stock filing
showed.        KKB Engineering Bhd. (KKB)  , an engineering and
construction group, slid 2.5 percent to 1.94 ringgit, the most
since May 23, after second-quarter net income fell 13 percent to
11.7 million ringgit as revenue declined.       Unisem (M) Bhd. (UNI MK), a semiconductor assembler, lost
0.7 percent to 1.39 ringgit, its lowest close since Jan. 5,
2010, after second-quarter profit dropped 75 percent to 12
million ringgit ($4.1 million).  To contact the reporter on this story:
Chan Tien Hin in  Kuala Lumpur  at 
